HMSU Net Label had its official launch on March 1st 2008. It is a long dreamed project, that finally made it to the public.

The idea to release quality works by HMSU&#039;s own artists and others dates back to 2006. It was originally proposed that we do regular releases with selections of unreleased tracks by independent artists. At the end of 2007 we finally decided that we have enough material to announce the start of our own Net Label, and promote it with a gig.

So here we are, kickin&#039; off with two releases - one brand new, and an old limited-edition one. The former was originally released as a special 100 promo copies CD, and was handed out at a gig with Spor back in 2006. The other release features five brand new tracks by leading Bulgarian artists: Cooh, Ogonek, Mocks, Digital Soul and Kigami
